Hi @aflorido and thanks for your Contribution !

Well, i have to say that some Test cases helped me more than the explanations ...
=> I'm worry about solvability within only 5 minutes ...

But, this exercice is pretty cool ...
=> I upvote for your job ;-) !

My C# solution (with DEBUG info) :
int K = int.Parse(Console.ReadLine());
int N = int.Parse(Console.ReadLine());
string[] inputs = Console.ReadLine().Split(' ');
Console.Error.WriteLine(K.ToString() + ", " + N.ToString() + " = " + string.Join(", ", inputs));
int KN = K > N ? N : K;
IEnumerable<int> lst = inputs.Take(KN+1).Select(int.Parse);
Console.Error.WriteLine("Tkn = " + string.Join(", ", lst.Select(i => i.ToString())));
if(K%2 == 1) lst = lst.Skip(1);
Console.Error.WriteLine("Skp = " + string.Join(", ", lst.Select(i => i.ToString())));
if(lst.Count() > 0) Console.WriteLine(lst.Max());
else Console.WriteLine("EMPTY");
